        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(mistral): add Monthly Plan menu bar metric (subscription usage)",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nCloses #1363.\r\n\r\nAdds support for Mistral's subscription (Vibe CLI / Codestral) usage in the menu bar, addressing the gap reported in the issue where only API spend was shown but not the monthly plan quota.\r\n\r\n- Adds a new **Monthly Plan** option to the Mistral \"Menu bar metric\" picker (alongside the renamed **Pay-as-you-go**)\r\n- Fetches `usage_percentage` from `console.mistral.ai/api-ui/trpc/billing.vibeUsage` using the same cookie already collected for the billing page\r\n- Displays the subscription usage % in the menu bar when Monthly Plan is selected (e.g. `3%`, with reset countdown)\r\n- Falls back gracefully if the vibe API is unavailable (non-fatal — existing cost display unaffected)\r\n- Exempts Mistral from the `isBalanceOnlyProvider` restriction so the new preference persists correctly\r\n\r\n<img width=\"384\" height=\"449\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f371509a-6942-4a7c-b34d-9f0bc3c2df3b\" />\r\n<img width=\"904\" height=\"862\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c4c6c2bf-3d93-489d-addd-d79ba0dce536\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n## Test plan\r\n\r\n- [ ] Enable Mistral with a Manual cookie containing `csrftoken`\r\n- [ ] Open provider settings → Mistral → Menu bar metric → select **Monthly Plan**\r\n- [ ] Verify preference sticks and menu bar shows subscription usage % with reset time\r\n- [ ] Verify **Pay-as-you-go** still shows `$X.XXXX` cost as before\r\n- [ ] Verify users without a monthly plan (vibe API fails) see no regression — app still loads cost data normally\r\n\r\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
